  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And-- but there was a refugee physician and his wife from Vienna who lived there as well.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he sort of shepherded over people who needed medical attention.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the other full-time job that I had was to queue up as a bedraggled, little French girl, which I was because I had no clothing to speak of, and queue up all day long, from one queue to the next.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I started early in the morning when the stores opened at 7:00 and queued up for bread, queued up for milk, queued up for sometimes even an egg or two.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And that was, it was a full-time occupation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because that was the only way you could really get food in-- in occupied Paris at the time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was no glamor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The Louver was sealed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The Eiffel Tower was closed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "All places of-- of culture were closed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And it was this city under siege, absolutely.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And so there we were from the beginning of August.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And finally, finally got our papers, our exit visas and-- and our passage for America early in December, December 6, if I'm correct, 1940.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And of course, the only way that we could get to our harbor at the time-- it had to be a neutral harbor.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It had to be a neutral ship that could sail across the Atlantic Ocean.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And so the only way to go was to take a train to the border of France to Spain and then traverse Spain all the way across and then into Portugal and go to Portugal and get a ship out of Lisbon.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "When we finally left Paris, there was a really emotional farewell to all our friends, and especially to this Leon Spitter who had helped us so very much.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
